HEADWORD: Zeitgeist
<hw>Zeit"geist`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.;
<ets>zeit</ets> time + <ets>geist</ets> spirit. See <er>Tide</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>; <er>Ghost</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>The spirit of
the time; the general intellectual and moral state or temper
characteristic of any period of time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

